Summary of THg and LOI model results

KVITENSE

2023-02-13

THg model without LOI

  • Harvards GEOS-Chem WetLoss_ variables are best predictors followed by catchment characteristics (precip, clay, runoff, temp), pH, and conductivity.
  • ~10 predictors
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.279
  • Minimum MAE: 0.18
  • Note: Results for this model are subject to change (though I dont think they would change much). If were going to use this model w/o LOI, I need to re-tune and re-run for consistency with methods for the other models (that evolved since running this original model). It also includes redundant predictors that have since been removed.

THg model with LOI included

  • Now LOI is top predictor and then the story is somewhat similar to the situation above, but GEOS-Chem predictors drop in relative importance compared to pH and catchment predictors.
  • This THg model with LOI included has better predictive accuracy than without LOI
  • Results and interpretation seem cleaner for this model relative to THg/LOI below because were accounting for LOI, but predictors for LOI are not mixed in with predictors for THg
  • ~14 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.247
  • Minimum MAE: 0.158

THg/LOI model

  • Interesting non-monotonic pattern in RMSE as predictors are removed - likely because some predictors are better for predicting THg vs.LOI.
  • RMSE seems to start to decline again when predictors associated with LOI but not THg are removed (around 8-11 preds): SN, NH4, InorgNWetDep, NO3.
  • Hg0DryDep is top predictor for THg/LOI - Hg0DryDep and HgPDryDep rose in importance relative to the WetLoss predictors
  • Elevation also rose in relative importance
  • Takes more variables to maintain best predictive performance, likely because we are predicting both THg and LOI, and LOI models show that more predictors are needed for LOI relative to THg.
  • ~ 29 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.268
  • Minimum MAE: 0.173

LOI model with GEOS-Chem predictors

  • Top 6 predictors are non-GEOS-Chem predictors
  • More predictors are generally retained for LOI than THg, probably because the GEOS-Chem variables are strong predictors of THg and less so for LOI.
  • Note that iterative removal of GEOS-Chem predictors doesnt usually strongly impact predictive accuracy.
  • ~24 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.234
  • Minimum MAE: 0.16

LOI w/ GEOS-Chem removed

  • Top 6 predictors are the exact same as above (all non-GEOS-Chem predictors), and the rest of the order is very similar if the GEOS-Chem predictors are ignored.
  • Note that removal of GEOS-Chem predictors doesnt impact best predictive accuracy for LOI.
  • ~23 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.234
  • Minimum MAE: 0.159
